<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#123#000055#      12.2#">Va. Code Ann. § 55-12.2</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_55-12.2"/><heading><desig>§ 55-12.2.</desig><title>When nonvested property interest or power of appointment created</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Except as provided in subsections B and C and in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-12.5"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -12.5">§ 55-12.5<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#      12.5#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, the time of creation of a nonvested property interest or a power of appointment is determined under general principles of property law.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> For the purposes of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-12.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -12.1">§§ 55-12.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#      12.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> through <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-12.6"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -12.6">55-12.6<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#      12.6#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, if there is a person who alone can exercise a power created by a governing instrument to become the unqualified beneficial owner of (i) a nonvested property interest or (ii) a property interest subject to a power of appointment described in subsection B or C in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-12.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -12.1">§ 55-12.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#      12.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, the nonvested property interest or power of appointment is created when the power to become the unqualified beneficial owner terminates.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>C.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> For the purposes of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-12.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -12.1">§§ 55-12.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#      12.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> through <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-12.6"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -12.6">55-12.6<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#      12.6#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, a nonvested property interest or a power of appointment arising from a transfer of property to a previously funded trust or other existing property arrangement is created when the nonvested property interest or power of appointment in the original contribution was created.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2000 VA CH 714"><content><span normalizedCite="2000 Va. Ch. 714">2000, c. 714<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2000#000714#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PV50-004G-K4CJ-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 55.</desig><title>PROPERTY AND CONVEYANCES</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 1.</desig><title>CREATION AND LIMITATION OF ESTATES; THEIR QUALITIES</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Estate, Gift &amp; Trust Law</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OENGNTY0MEQ2RTU2NDA2NTk4QjcyNzI2NTBERUU3NUI7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6Q0VEQ0U4QTFCMzc1NDkyQjgzMjNBQUJFREFDOEJCOTA7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NUQ4NThEMTk0MTQ4NDM3N0FGOEM5RkU2QUQ4RjA1MkQ</classCode></classificationItem></classificationItem></classification><classificationGroup classificationScheme="indexing-terms"><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Business &amp; Corporate Compliance</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MUFEMUQ2QTA1OUZCNEE5RjkzNTA2RERFMUNEOTk1RTI7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem score="90"><className>Real Property</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QUUyRTcxRURBNEY2NEE2MDk3QzBCNzRDOEY0NTZDQzk7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MUFEMUQ2QTA1OUZCNEE5RjkzNTA2RERFMUNEOTk1RTI</classCode></classificationItem></classific